  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Myanmar: Strengthening the Capacity of Legal Practitioners for Improved Justice Service Delivery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enable legal practitioners to understand the legal framework and best practices relating to trauma-informed lawyering, vulnerable populations, evidentiary issues, and investigative and trial techniques. 2) To enable legal practitioners to collaborate to document challenges and solutions in preserving fair trials rights for clients.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Legal practitioners (including lawyers, paralegals, and others working to support justice seekers).
Indirect beneficiaries: Clients or justice seekers accessing help and representation from the direct beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to enable legal practitioners to apply best practices to safeguard their clients&apos; fair trial rights</narrative>
  </description>
